&quot;en&quot;}" data-component-name="EmbeddedPostToDOM"><a class="embedded-post" native="true" href="https://lillianli.substack.com/p/a-future-history-of-china-in-the?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_campaign=post_embed&amp;utm_medium=web"><div class="embedded-post-header"><img class="embedded-post-publication-logo" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_56,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe34121c4-fa15-41d2-bea1-69182c1fc07a_1125x1125.png" loading="lazy"><span class="embedded-post-publication-name">Chinese Characteristics</span></div><div class="embedded-post-title-wrapper"><div class="embedded-post-title">A future history of China in the 2020s</div></div><div class="embedded-post-cta-wrapper"><span class="embedded-post-cta">Read more</span></div><div class="embedded-post-meta">a year ago &#183; 44 likes &#183; 12 comments &#183; Lillian Li</div></a></div><p>It is easiest to be pessimistic during bleak times; during this year, everyone had their knives out for China. Investors should see through sentiments for the underlying fundamentals, and this was my humble contribution to that effort. Things are never as good or as bad as it seems, especially about China.</p><p><em>The most personal piece:</em> <strong>The next chapter</strong></p><div class="embedded-post-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;id&quot;:62004954,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://lillianli.substack.com/p/the-next-chapter&quot;,&quot;publication_id&quot;:80709,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Chinese Characteristics&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e34121c4-fa15-41d2-bea1-69182c1fc07a_1125x1125.png&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;The next chapter&quot;,&quot;truncated_body_text&quot;:null,&quot;date&quot;:&quot;2022-07-01T10:00:58.703Z&quot;,&quot;like_count&quot;:71,&quot;comment_count&quot;:32,&quot;bylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:3249443,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Lillian Li&quot;,&quot;previous_name&quot;:null,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/20b913eb-e477-43cb-a0dd-9c26ec0b8698_1088x728.png&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Refactoring. Private company investment @ Baillie Gifford. Prev - Eight Roads Ventures, Salesforce Ventures, LEK Consulting. Cambridge and LSE alum. \n@lillianmli\n&quot;,&quot;profile_set_up_at&quot;:&quot;2021-07-16T08:12:18.387Z&quot;,&quot;publicationUsers&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:90983,&quot;user_id&quot;:3249443,&quot;publication_id&quot;:80709,&quot;role&quot;:&quot;admin&quot;,&quot;public&quot;:true,&quot;is_primary&quot;:false,&quot;publication&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:80709,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Chinese Characteristics&quot;,&quot;subdomain&quot;:&quot;lillianli&quot;,&quot;custom_domain&quot;:null,&quot;custom_domain_optional&quot;:false,&quot;hero_text&quot;:&quot;Chinese tech longform analysis&quot;,&quot;logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e34121c4-fa15-41d2-bea1-69182c1fc07a_1125x1125.png&quot;,&quot;author_id&quot;:3249443,&quot;theme_var_background_pop&quot;:&quot;#d10000&quot;,&quot;created_at&quot;:&quot;2020-08-11T11:50:54.748Z&quot;,&quot;rss_website_url&quot;:null,&quot;email_from_name&quot;:&quot;Lillian from Chinese Characteristics&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;Lillian Li&quot;,&quot;founding_plan_name&quot;:&quot;Outsourced analyst&quot;,&quot;community_enabled&quot;:true,&quot;invite_only&quot;:false,&quot;payments_state&quot;:&quot;disabled&quot;}}],&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:null,&quot;inviteAccepted&quot;:true}],&quot;utm_campaign&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;language&quot;:&quot;en&quot;}" data-component-name="EmbeddedPostToDOM"><a class="embedded-post" native="true" href="https://lillianli.substack.com/p/the-next-chapter?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_campaign=post_embed&amp;utm_medium=web"><div class="embedded-post-header"><img class="embedded-post-publication-logo" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_56,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe34121c4-fa15-41d2-bea1-69182c1fc07a_1125x1125.png" loading="lazy"><span class="embedded-post-publication-name">Chinese Characteristics</span></div><div class="embedded-post-title-wrapper"><div class="embedded-post-title">The next chapter</div></div><div class="embedded-post-cta-wrapper"><span class="embedded-post-cta">Read more</span></div><div class="embedded-post-meta">2 years ago &#183; 71 likes &#183; 32 comments &#183; Lillian Li</div></a></div><p>In mid-2022, I bailed on being a thought leader and returned to gainful employment. One could argue that I followed the well-trodden path of cashing on my<a href="https://alexdanco.com/2021/07/08/michael-dwight-and-andy-the-three-aesthetics-of-the-creative-class/"> Very Online social status</a> by being captured by the Establishment. After you spend two years outside the matrix, you start to appreciate the little things about office life - like free fruits and dying with a pension. It turned out that I do indeed<a href="https://identity-mag.com/i-dont-dream-of-labor-rise-of-anti-work-movement-explained/"> dream of labour</a>.</p><p>Jokes aside, writing for you has been a pleasure, and I wouldn&#8217;t have left for just any Establishment. I want you to know that BG&#8217;s free fruits have been great so far.</p><p><strong>Verdict on my 2022 predictions</strong></p><p>In the spirit of intellectual honesty, I wrote this list of 2022 predictions in December 2021. They were all exceedingly sensible, but 2022 was not a sensible year, and I was off for most of them.</p><ul><li><p>Regulators established the company pecking order and will continue to implement and strengthen policies to match government objectives</p></li><li><p><a href="https://lillianli.substack.com/p/prediction-agriculture-tech-is-going">Agricultural tech</a> and subsequent rural development that supports common prosperity will become a trend that generates much PR attention</p></li><li><p>Hyperreality <a href="https://lillianli.substack.com/p/premium-the-multiverse-of-metaverse">metaverse</a> hype will persist while treading a fine line</p></li><li><p>Enterprise services / B2B software / cloud adoption will take centre stage as consumer tech maintains lowered profiles on their existing service lines</p></li><li><p>Low-carbon technology for both consumers and enterprises will become a must-have</p></li><li><p>The lines between e-commerce and content players will continue to blur until everyone&#8217;s fighting everyone else</p></li></ul><p>In terms of 2023 and what may come then, I&#8217;ll leave the opining for next week.</p><p>Sooner or later, we all grow up to be disappointments to our former selves. Last year, I ended with a resolution to publish more frequently in 2022 and then, life happened. From June onwards, my public output has dwelled between a writing sabbatical, the new job and travelling. Gentle readers, I will make a much more concerted effort in 2023.</p><p>Here&#8217;s to 2022; you&#8217;ve mostly sucked (I believe that&#8217;s the technical term). And here&#8217;s to 2023; may you bring us something good.</p><p>Happy new year!</p><div class="footnote" data-component-name="FootnoteToDOM"><a id="footnote-1" href="#footnote-anchor-1" class="footnote-number" contenteditable="false" target="_self">1</a><div class="footnote-content"><p>Long-time readers will recognise these frameworks from <a href="https://lillianli.substack.com/p/bilibili-deep-dive">Bilibili</a>,<a href="https://lillianli.substack.com/p/premium-special-gamification-of-chinese"> Gamification of consumer apps</a> and<a href="https://lillianli.substack.com/p/premium-your-superapp-needs-a-content?s=w"> Your superapp needs a content strategy</a></p></div></div><div class="footnote" data-component-name="FootnoteToDOM"><a id="footnote-2" href="#footnote-anchor-2" class="footnote-number" contenteditable="false" target="_self">2</a><div class="footnote-content"><p><a href="https://observer.com/2016/11/chinas-new-ultra-unreal-fiction-only-strange-art-can-explain-it/">Chaohuan</a> (translated to &#8220;Ultra-unreal&#8221;) is a genre of Chinese fiction that reads like sci-fi as it tries to describe the absurdity and hyperboles of modern china life.</p></div></div><div class="footnote" data-component-name="FootnoteToDOM"><a id="footnote-3" href="#footnote-anchor-3" class="footnote-number" contenteditable="false" target="_self">3</a><div class="footnote-content"><p>Something this Substack is sometimes guilty of</p><p></p></div></div>